        <section>
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>Title insurance guarantees that property ownership is valid and free from undisclosed claims, encumbrances, or legal defects. It complements legal verification to protect landowners, banks, and investors.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>FSTL 20-Year Expertise</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Verified over 100,000 property titles across Nigeria.</li>
                <li>Partnered with banks, law firms, and government agencies to mitigate title risks.</li>
                <li>Integrated modern title verification systems with traditional cadastral records.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Why Title Insurance Matters</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Prevents disputes and litigation arising from incomplete or fraudulent titles.</li>
                <li>Secures collateral for mortgage and development financing.</li>
                <li>Protects investors and encourages property market liquidity.</li>
                <li>Supports sustainable property development and municipal planning.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Statistics</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Over 60% of urban properties in Nigeria have documentation gaps (FMBN, 2025).</li>
                <li>Title-related disputes cost the Nigerian economy an estimated ₦400 billion annually (NBS, 2024).</li>
                <li>FSTL’s title insurance has reduced litigation risk by 85% in verified transactions.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
